snapraid-daily (1.5.4-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Updated Mutt Email Config Documentation to add guidelines for
    using Fastmail.com and a Self-Hosted ntfy server.

  * Added a "smart_report" parameter to the configuration file. This will
    call "snapraid smart" after the script completes if enabled. Note
    that this requires sudo to be set up or the script to be ran as
    root.

  * Added a "spin_down_disks" parameter to the configuration file. This
    call "snapraid down" after the script completes if enabled. Note
    that this requires sudo to be setup or the script to be ran as
    root.

  * Updated manual entries and main README to add details about the
    new configuration file parameters and how to set up sudo to use
    them as a non-root user.

  * Added recommended package dependency on sudo.

 -- Mark <mark9000@fastmail.org>  Sun, 19 Oct 2025 15:13:55 +0100

snapraid-daily (1.5.3-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Added a check for an update from the Github page. Now when the
    script is called, it will do a check to see if curl is installed
    and if so, it will check the Github page for a newer version
    and notify the user by way of printing a notice and also adding
    a line to the email log.

  * Also added a "disable_update_check" parameter to the config file
    to disable the update check functionality if desired.

  * Updated default config file and example that incorporates multiple
    hooks.

  * Removed duplicate systemd example files from systemd-examples docs
    directory.
    - Improved examples in sample systemd timer file.

  * Added section to unset all config file variables before the config
    file is read, and also all variables set by arguments to the script.
    This prevents issues in the unlikely event those exact variables are
    set via export commands externally before calling then script.

  * Made config file error detection more robust. The script will now
    exit if syntax errors are present in the config file.

  * Improved Cron Documentation.

  * Added recommended package dependency on curl.

  * Minor Code Cleanup
    - Silence which commands, reduce linecount, trim comments.

